properties.areaDesc: Cape Decision to Salisbury Sound Coastal Area
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 29 at 3:19PM AKST until January 30 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...South to southwesterly gusts to 65 mph.

* WHERE...Baranof Island including Sitka and Port Alexander.

* WHEN...From 3 AM to 6 PM AKST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power
lines. Power outages are possible. Travel will be difficult.
Objects may be blown around in the wind. Improperly moored
boats may break loose.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO NOON AKST THURSDAY
